I was really hoping this dish would live up to all the positive reviews. For me, it was rather disappointing. To start I followed the recipe almost as written. I say almost because when I got home I realized that I had forgotten to get the coleslaw mix. I decided that a trip back to the store was not in the books, so I did not make the slaw. I made the the rest of the recipe as written, I even had the hot smoked paprika. My main complaint was that the chicken was way to sweet. Maybe the slaw would have balanced out the sweetness of the chicken/veggie mixture, but on its own I found it overwhelmingly sweet to the point that I wouldn't use this rub as written on anything else. Ever. On a personal note, I now know that I don't care for the flavor of Chipotle chilis (or maybe it was the adobo sauce) but either way-yuck. The sour cream was really easy to make but it was not for me. Overall, maybe I didn't like the recipe because I didn't have the slaw or maybe it just wasn't for me. But either way I was so underwhelmed that I don't think this one will get another attempt.

