Rating: 3
This is a shockingly good recipe for how easy it is. The rub is great on the chicken (I used a grill pan with excellent results). A mix of hot and smoked Paprika is a fine substitute. Since we're not zucchini fans, I sauteed white onions with the red peppers. This added some nice sweetness to the dish. Corn tortillas are a must for yet another level of flavor. Decrease the amount of sour cream (or in our case, fat free Greek yogurt) and/or increase your chili amount. It doesn't need to be overwhelming but you want the smoke and heat flavor. The slaw is not meant as a side dish; you need to put it in the tacos. Making it last adds a great crunch texture to the tacos but the slaw also tastes fine and adds citrus after it wilts. Will definitely make frequently; most certainly will impress friends. Very authentic dish.

