Rating: 4
This is a great, easy weeknight recipe that I will definitely make again many times in the future. It would also make for excellent kebabs! A few variations: 1) I used nonfat Fage's greek yogurt instead of sour cream, which is equally delicious and much lighter/healthier. 2) I turned the rub into more of a marinade by tossing 1" chicken cubes with a little canola oil, sprinkling with the spice mixture, tossing to coat and refrigerating in a ziploc bag for about 3 hours (did the same thing in a separate bag with the veggies). This made the chicken very tender and flavorful. 3) I didn't make the slaw and didn't miss it at all. 4) For the veggies, I used red onion, red and yellow peppers and zucchini. Next time I'll omit the zucchini as it felt out of place. The onions were the best part... highly recommend adding. This also tastes delicious served over homemade baked corn tortilla chips with spanish rice, beans and a little cheese... spicy multi-layer nachos, yum!

