Rating: 3
This recipe is very good, but a few notes. First of all, for 1 lb. of chicken, 1.5 cups of sour cream is WAY too much. And for 1.5 cups of sour cream, 1 T. of chipotle chilis is WAY too little. I would recommend cutting the sour cream in half unless you want to be figuring out how to use the rest of it. Next is the rub. I found the onion powder to be extremely overwhelming. I actually re-made the rub without the onion powder, and with half the garlic powder. Again, it turned out to be too much rub for a pound of chicken, but I'm not too upset about having extra because I can use it on something else this week. You definitely need the smoked paprika, it makes a huge difference. Next, I left out the zucchini (didn't want the mushy texture), and instead grilled some onions. Turned out to be a great combination. Finally, one pound of chicken does not make "6 servings". I would say it serves three at most. And the corn tortillas are a MUST. If you've never had them, I promise you that once you have, you'll never go back to flour tortillas.

